President Barack Obama has proclaimed May 2013 as Jewish American Heritage Month. In his proclamation, he highlights the historical contributions and achievements of Jewish Americans in shaping the United States. He references President George Washington's commitment to religious freedom and emphasizes the importance of inclusivity and equality for all Americans, regardless of their background or faith. Obama recognizes the impact of Jewish immigrants on American society and their role in advancements in science, the arts, and social progress. He calls upon all Americans to learn more about Jewish American heritage and celebrate it through various programs and activities.